<span id="an_7:40">7:40</span> one male of the goats for a sin-offering;

<span id="an_7:41">7:41</span> and for the sacrifice of peace-offerings,
two oxen, five rams, five he-goats, five he-lambs a year old: this was
the oblation of Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.

<span id="an_7:42">7:42</span> On the sixth day Eliasaph the son of
Deuel, prince of the children of Gad:

<span id="an_7:43">7:43</span> his oblation was one silver platter, the
weight whereof was a hundred and thirty \[shekels\], one silver bowl of
seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of
fine flour mingled with oil for a meal-offering;

<span id="an_7:44">7:44</span> one golden spoon of ten \[shekels\], full
of incense;

<span id="an_7:45">7:45</span> one young bullock, one ram, one he-lamb a
